SIMPLE: probationer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Probationer
<hw>Pro*ba"tion*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>One who is undergoing probation; one who is on
trial; a novice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>While yet a young <qex>probationer</qex>,⟦br⟧
And candidate of heaven.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A student in divinity, who, having received
certificates of good morals and qualifications from his university, is
admitted to several trials by a presbytery, and, on acquitting himself
well, is licensed to preach.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Probationership</ent>⟦br⟧
